OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5Flighting up Soho           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, To this day, the streets of London are 
OL,6, illuminated by a Welsh miner who       
OL,7, decided he'd had enough of the dark.   
OL,9,FRichard Bracey, from Mountain Ash,     
OL,10,FRhondda Cynon Taff, worked down the    
OL,11,FTredegar mines in the 1940s.           
OL,13,FAfter "hating" the work, he travelled  
OL,14,Fto London by horse and cart and his    
OL,15,Fneon signs soon became a fixture of the
OL,16,FSoho's notoriously seedy nightlife.    
OL,18,FNow owned by his grandson, the company 
OL,19,FRichard started 70 years ago ships     
OL,20,Fsigns to all corners of the world.     
